e nation.%0a%0a%0a%0aJuly 10, 2000%0aH. J. Heinz Company introduces green ketchup.%0a%0a%0a%0aJuly 25, 2000%0aDan Rooney, Pittsburgh Steeler owner, joins his father, Art, in the Football Hall of Fame.%0a%0a%0a%0aAugust 16, 2000%0aTurner Dairy of Penn Hills, Pa. discontinues home delivery. The last dairy to do so.%0a%0a%0a%0aSeptember 5, 2000%0aCenter for Sports Medicine of the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center opens at the combined Steeler and University of Pittsburgh training facility on the South Side.%0a%0a%0a%0aSeptember 6, 2000%0aPittsburgh Roman Catholic Diocese agrees to sell St. Nicholas Church (the first Croatian Roman Catholic Church in the United States) to permit the widening of Route 28.%0a%0a%0a%0aSeptember 12, 2000%0aWilliam R. Johnson becomes the fifth chairman in the 131-year history of H. J. Heinz Company.%0a%0a%0a%0aSeptember 19, 2000%0aPNC begins to move its headquarters from Tenth and Duquesne Way to First and Grant Streets.%0a%0a%0a%0aOctober 1, 2000%0aPittsburgh Pirates play last game at Three Rivers Stadium losing to the Chicago Cubs 10-9.%0a%0a%0a%0aOctober 26, 2000%0aCarnegie Science Center plans a 160,000 square foot expansion.%0a%0a%0a%0aNovember 1, 2000%0aLord and Taylor Department Store opens in the former Mellon National Bank Building on Smithfield Street.%0a%0a%0a%0aNovember 13, 2000%0aFormer Penguin Hockey star, Joey Mullen is inducted into the Hockey Hall of Fame.%0a%0a%0a%0aDecember 1, 2000%0aGwen Mellon, co-founder with husband Dr. William L. Mellon, Jr. of the Albert Schweitzer Hospital in Haiti, dies.%0a%0a%0a%0aDecember 7, 2000%0aPennsylvania Historical and Museum Commission purchases boundary land around Bushy Run Battlefield.%0a%0a%0a%0aDecember 8, 2000%0aMario Lemieux announces plans to come out of retirement to play hockey.%0a%0a%0a%0aDecember 16, 2000%0aSteelers defeat the Washington Redskins 24-3 at the last football game at Three Rivers Stadium.%0a%0a%0a%0aDecember 30, 2000%0aThe Queen of England knights Anthony O'